entries.name: ZKsync
entries.description: The main contract defining the Layer 2. Operator actions like commiting blocks, providing ZK proofs and executing batches ultimately target this contract which then processes transactions. During batch execution it processes L1 --> L2 and L2 --> L1 transactions. isPermanentRollup was set to true in this contract which prevents changing the DA mode to Validium in the future.

values.isPermanentRollupString: . isPermanentRollup was set to true in this contract which prevents changing the DA mode to Validium in the future.

getTransactionFilterer.description: This contract must expose the ITransactionFilterer interface (see Mailbox facet) and is used for censoring transactions pushed from L1 to L2.

IsPorterAvailableStatus.description: zkPorter is a volition-like contruction and changes the zk proof input requirements.

isPermanentRollup.description: true means that the DA mode cannot be changed to Validium in the future. compliant DAValidator pairs for the permanent rollup mode are defined/enforced by the RollupDAManager contract.

getProtocolVersion.description: Protocol version, increments with each protocol upgrade.

getVerifierParams.description: Verifier parameters used for proving batches.

arg.1: . isPermanentRollup was set to true in this contract which prevents changing the DA mode to Validium in the future.

entries.name: L1ERC20Bridge_wstETH
entries.description: Bridge for depositing wrapped stETH (Lido) to ZKsync Era. These deposits and withdrawals do not go through the shared Bridge.

entries.name: L1ERC20Bridge
entries.description: Legacy bridge for depositing ERC20 tokens to ZKsync Era. Forwards deposits and withdrawals to the BridgeHub.

entries.name: Bridgehub
entries.description: The main registry (hub) for all the contracts in the ZK stack cluster and central entrypoint for bridge transactions. Stores important mappings like from chainId to diamond address, from chainId to parent CTM, from chainId to base token etc. A clone of Bridgehub is also deployed on each L2 chain, but this clone is only used on settlement layers.

chainsCreated.description: All new chains created go thorugh the central bridgehub and are stored here with their respective STMs.

settlementLayers.description: New settlement layers and their whitelist status. Chains can be migrated to whitelisted settlement layers by their chain admin.

entries.name: L2AssetRouter
entries.description: Bridge routing contract that exists once on every zk stack chain and keeps mappings of assets to their escrows (asset handlers) and deployment trackers.

entries.name: MessageRoot
entries.description: Aggregates remote bridge message roots from all ZK stack chains. To be used with the Gateway when deployed.

receivedPermissions.description: revert batches for any connected chain (ZK cluster Admin role).

administrate operator roles for this chain in the ValidatorTimelock, manage fees, apply predefined upgrades, manage censorship through a TransactionFilterer, set DA mode, migrate the chain to whitelisted settlement layers (Chain Admin role).

entries.name: RelayedSLDAValidator
entries.description: Plugs into the DAValidator interface of zk stack Diamond contracts. This 'DA validator' simply checks correct formatting and encoding of data and relays it via the L1Messenger to L1 to guarantee data availability.

entries.name: RollupDAManager
entries.description: Simple registry for allowed DA address pairs for the 'rollup' data availability mode (can be permanently enforced with isPermanentRollup=true). Rollup DA address pairs (especially the L1 part) usually point to contracts that validate if data was made available on Ethereum.

entries.name: L1GenesisUpgrade
entries.description: Diamond implementation code to initialize new ZK chains. Used to set their chainID.

entries.name: ServerNotifier
entries.description: A simple contract that can be called by the ChainAdmin to emit notifications about chain migrations.

entries.name: ChainTypeManager
entries.description: Defines L2 diamond contract versions, creation and upgrade data and the proof system for all ZK stack chains connected to it. ZK chains are children of this central contract and can only upgrade to versions that were previously registered here. The current protocol version is 0,29,2.

entries.name: DualVerifier
entries.description: A router contract for verifiers. Routes verification requests to gateway:0xD837976329d59057b27192f0cF6c8f357143670A or gateway:0xfA7c56B328bEb5deB9218f3a4b60ADc59Bb6Ad8d depending on the supplied proof type.

verificationKeyHash.description: Verification key hash for the PLONK verifier ONLY (backwards compatibility).

During batch execution it processes L1 --> L2 and L2 --> L1 transactions. isPermanentRollup was set to true in this contract which prevents changing the DA mode to Validium in the future.

entries.name: L1VerifierFflonk
entries.description: Verifies a zk-SNARK proof using an implementation of the fflonk proof system.

verificationKeyHash.description: keccak256 hash of the verification keys.

entries.name: ZKsyncValidatorTimelock
entries.description: Intermediary contract between the *Validators* and the central diamond contract that delays block execution (ie withdrawals and other L2 --> L1 messages) by 0s.

receivedPermissions.description: commit, prove, execute, revert batches directly in the main Diamond contract. This role is typically held by a proxying ValidatorTimelock.
set critical contract addresses for the shared cluster, register settlement layers, pause and unpause migrations and the bridge and manage zk chain registration.
manage allowed rollup DA pairs (allowed to be used by rollups in permanent rollup mode).

manage the shared ValidatorTimelock contract address and the admin role, register and execute upgrades (and set their deadlines), freeze, revert batches and set permissioned validators and fee params for all connected chains.

entries.name: L1VerifierPlonk
entries.description: Verifies a zk-SNARK proof using an implementation of the PlonK proof system.
